{"model": "Devstral Small 2 24B", "runtime": "mlx", "prompt_name": "logic_ages__t3_cot", "prompt_tokens": 89, "generation_tokens": 254, "prompt_tps": 422.72821322199366, "generation_tps": 39.25090876858963, "peak_memory_gb": 13.529404524, "wall_time_sec": 6.727340249999543, "output": "Let's solve the problem step by step.\n\n1. Let Bob's current age be \\( B \\) years.\n2. Since Alice is twice as old as Bob, Alice's current age is \\( 2B \\) years.\n3. In 10 years, Bob's age will be \\( B + 10 \\) years.\n4. In 10 years, Alice's age will be \\( 2B + 10 \\) years.\n5. According to the problem, in 10 years, Alice will be 1.5 times as old as Bob. So, we can write the equation:\n   \\[\n   2B + 10 = 1.5(B + 10)\n   \\]\n6. Let's solve the equation:\n   \\[\n   2B + 10 = 1.5B + 15\n   \\]\n   \\[\n   2B - 1.5B = 15 - 10\n   \\]\n   \\[\n   0.5B = 5\n   \\]\n   \\[\n   B = \\frac{5}{0.5} = 10\n   \\]\n\nANSWER: 10", "error": null, "prompt_hash": "a33ec0efd7f9", "quant": "4bit"}
